The approach here is a little indelicate. If ever an article needed show-not-tell writing, this is it- subtlety is your friend. Just dumping an Inca death god rock in our laps 1/3 of the way in ruined any hope of build up. I'd recommend some shuffling- maybe even remove the "Note: Though the wreck is…" paragraph and rely on the existing email to point in that direction, maybe even add in one or two more SMALL bits of correspondence.

The one other specific recommendation I can make is to remove the parenthetical explanations of the three colored "zones" around the wreck- Foundation jargon can be a lot more interesting without explicit definition. Additionally, I might recommend using yellow, red, and black / dark / something more ominous instead of yellow, orange, and red. Perhaps even ???, kill, and quarantine if you prefer to be explicit. If you use color names without parentheticals but still want to make clear that there are deaths in the second zone, you might add some note about proper disposal of bodies from that area to make sure they don't end up too close to the wreck.







