I agree that the overtness of the "Inca death god" angle is not ideal, but I'm not sure how it could be changed to fix that. Expunging the bit about "He said Supai was their new God, the god of the dead. He said Supai would be our God, in time." might help - it's a little corny.

More nitpicky suggestions:

- "My friend Mike told me…" needs a tone-related tweak, to something more like "Mike █████ told me" or "Seaman █████ told me". This is a Foundation naval officer, not a ten-year-old.

- In the quoted correspondence, "girl's" should be " girls' ", if you're talking about two girls' possessions. If you're not, it should be rephrased to make that clear.

- I'm not sure whether "early 1500's" refers to early in the period 1500-1509 or 1500-1599. If the latter, "early 16th century" would fit the desired tone better.

- "GPS coordinates" is a really awkward phrase, given the fact that GPS systems don't use any distinct set of coordinates. Trimming the "GPS" and changing the blackboxes to the correct length to accomodate a ██º██'██"N ███º██'██"W coordinate format would be good.







